Package: PNADCperiods
Title: Identify Reference Periods in Brazil's PNADC Survey Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rogerio", "Barbosa", email = "rogerio.barbosa@iesp.uerj.br", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6796-4547")),
    person("Marcos", "Hecksher", email = "mdhecksher@gmail.com", role = c("aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2992-1252"))
           )
Description: Identifies reference periods (months, fortnights, and weeks) in
    Brazil's quarterly PNADC (Pesquisa Nacional por Amostra de Domicilios
    Continua) survey data and computes calibrated weights for sub-quarterly
    analysis. The core algorithm uses IBGE's "Parada TÃ©cnica" (technical break)
    rules combined with respondent birthdates to determine which temporal period
    each survey observation refers to. Period identification follows a nested
    hierarchy enforced by construction: fortnights require months, weeks require
    fortnights. Achieves ~97% monthly determination rate when using stacked
    multi-quarter data. Strict fortnight and week rates are lower (~6% and ~1.5%
    respectively) as they cannot leverage cross-quarter panel aggregation.
    Experimental strategies (probabilistic assignment and UPA aggregation) can
    boost fortnight rates to ~27% and week rates to ~2%. The package provides
    adaptive hierarchical weight calibration (4/2/1 cell levels for month/
    fortnight/week) with period-specific smoothing to produce survey weights
    calibrated to IBGE SIDRA population totals.
